## üö® CRITICAL RULES

### 1. Contract-First Development
- ‚úÖ **Define proto contract first** before implementing services
- ‚úÖ **Generate code from proto** (don't write manually)
- ‚úÖ **Version proto contracts** if breaking changes needed
- ‚ùå **Never bypass gRPC** for direct HTTP calls

### 2. Type Safety
- ‚úÖ **Use generated types** from proto files
- ‚úÖ **Validate message types** at service boundaries
- ‚úÖ **Handle errors gracefully** (gRPC status codes)

### 3. Network Security
- ‚úÖ **Use Railway's private network** for service-to-service calls
- ‚úÖ **Use TLS in production** (insecure only for local dev)
- ‚úÖ **Authenticate requests** if needed (add auth to proto)

### 4. Error Handling
- ‚úÖ **Use gRPC status codes** (OK, INVALID_ARGUMENT, NOT_FOUND, etc.)
- ‚úÖ **Return structured errors** in response messages
- ‚úÖ **Implement retry logic** with exponential backoff
- ‚úÖ **Log all gRPC errors** for debugging

